title: Reginald Rushin - Memorial Day Weekend - Campaign Kickoff

address_lines: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
location.venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details

description:
Join us this Memorial Day weekend for the official kickoff event launching Reginald Rushin’s campaign to win the Atlanta City Council seat for District 11! This gathering is the first step in building a strong, community-driven campaign focused on bringing positive change to our district.

Reginald Rushin, a proud Marine Corps veteran, brings the values of loyalty, discipline, leadership, and teamwork to his campaign. Guided by the motto "Semper Fi" ("Always Faithful"), Reginald is committed to serving our community with integrity and dedication. At this event, we will also honor and celebrate all veterans, including Reginald, for their service to our country.

Come meet Reginald in person and hear about his vision to make District 11 safer, more equitable, and prosperous. His priorities include improving city services, supporting economic growth, enhancing public safety, expanding affordable housing, and increasing access to healthcare—all through transparent and community-focused leadership.

This kickoff event will have a warm, Southern-style atmosphere where neighbors, friends, and families can ask questions, share ideas, and find ways to get involved in the campaign. Whether you care about neighborhood improvements, small business support, or public safety, this is your opportunity to connect and help shape the future of District 11.

Together, let’s honor the true spirit of Memorial Day by coming together as one inclusive community to launch Reginald Rushin’s campaign for City Council. This event marks the beginning of a movement where every voice matters and every resident has the opportunity to thrive. Your participation is essential to kicking off this campaign and making a lasting impact.

title: Knock on Doors in Racine!
description:
### Join us to talk to our neighbors and fight back against the Republican agenda!

In Racine, we have a huge opportunity to flip State Senate District 21—one of the **most competitive** districts in the entire state! Under current Republican leadership, the state legislature has rejected expanding Medicaid, slashed public education funding, and restricted access to reproductive health care. But we can change that. 

If we start connecting with voters about the issues that matter to them this summer, we’ll have the power we need to flip this district next year. We can decide control of the Wisconsin State Senate and elect Democrats who will protect our health care, invest in public education, and stand up for reproductive freedom.

**During this event, we’ll knock on doors and have powerful conversations with our neighbors.** We’ll listen to their concerns, share what’s at stake in the State Senate, and invite them to join our team. **Sign up here to build power in Racine County and fight for a better future for all Wisconsinites!**

NO KINGS is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption from Trump and his allies. We’ve watched as they’ve cracked down on free speech, detained people for their political views, threatened to deport American citizens, and defied the courts. They’ve done this all while continuing to serve and enrich their billionaire allies.

title: Protest 287(g) in PWC
description:
May 21st 2025
4:45pm-7:30pm
Adult Detention Center - 9320 Lee Ave, Manassas

In response to the Manassas GOP’s call to reinstate the 287(g) program at the Prince William-Manassas Regional Jail, local Democratic leaders, immigrant rights advocates, and concerned residents will gather peacefully outside the Jail Board meeting on Wednesday, May 21, 2025 at 6pm, to reject policies rooted in racial profiling, fear-mongering, and the criminalization of immigrant communities.

We stand for a Prince William County and City of Manassas that welcomes all residents, regardless of immigration status. The 287(g) program has historically eroded trust between law enforcement and immigrant families, making communities less safe and more divided.

The PWCDC Latino Caucus and community advocates firmly opposes any efforts to revive the 287(g) agreement, which was discontinued in 2020 due to widespread concerns about civil rights violations, discriminatory enforcement, and costly legal challenges. Reinstating it would represent a dangerous step backward and undermine the values of inclusion and due process.

Attendees of the counter-protest are encouraged to bring signs, wear green as a symbol of unity, and submit public comments demanding humane, community-centered approaches to public safety.

We will not be silent while extremist agendas threaten the dignity and safety of our neighbors. We call on all people of conscience to stand with us in solidarity.

title: Remember George Floyd

address_lines: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
location.venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details

description:
Conservative pundits and Trump ally Elon Musk have promoted a push to secure a federal pardon for Chauvin in recent months. On March 4, right-wing commentator Ben Shapiro launched an online petition on his video podcast and X, urging viewers to support the effort. Musk shared a clip from the podcast on his X page, writing “Something to think about.” Chauvin, 49, is currently serving concurrent state and federal prison sentences for killing Floyd, 46, during a police incident in which he knelt on Floyd’s neck and back for more than nine minutes. Chauvin was convicted by a 12-member jury on state charges for unintentional second-degree murder, third-degree murder, and second-degree manslaughter. He later pleaded guilty in a federal civil rights case for depriving Floyd of his rights.

Wednesday, May 21st, at 4 pm we need an
ALL OUT to the Hall of (In) Justice.
Calling all folks, people who stayed tapped in since 2020 and those who we have missed- we need you now more than ever! Join us in the streets and STAY in the streets!
Five years. Five years since a life was stolen. Five years of grief and pain for his family.
Five years since the world stood up and gave a clarion call #DefundThePolice because #BlackLivesMatter.
We still say #GeorgeFloyd and we fight in his name, always.
As there is talk of a pardon for his killer, Derek Chauvin it is only symbolic of a larger problem. Police everywhere are increasing their violence on the streets and on campuses as students protest genocide.
Simultaneously, police are given the green light by DAs, AGs, and the president to further their violence and corruption all while further criminalizing organizers, protestors, and activists.
But we demand not only an end to this shift, but the very systems that uphold it all.

title: MUSK/TRUMP PROTEST
description:
Help us protest the world's most sensitive billionaire as he unconstitutionally dismantles our great country! It's easier to get at Trump through Elon Musk, and we're winning!  Elon may be "stepping down", but DOGE continues to destroy!

Some notes about this specific location for protesting:
- It is 100% legal to protest on the grass, directly across from Tesla.  Security and Glendale police are very friendly, and they are there to protect us from instigators. The police speak through me, so they don’t create conflict by approaching the crowd.

- The Americana greens is actually a public park. But we are prohibited from standing in front of Tesla, or in the trolley road. Failure to do so could technically lead to arrest. Obviously walking up to and away from the protest with signs is fine. It’s nothing to stress about, just be cool.

- There are shoppers and kids there. Please do not use profanity on your signs or from your mouth

- Glendale law prohibits signs with poles or sticks that are thicker than 1/4". So thin wood is fine! Larger is considered a possible weapon.

Feel free to come up to me with any concerns during (or before) the protest.  

If you want to lead chants, go for it!  Let's have fun!

- Joel

Signs with simple messages and big bold type are easiest to read for passing cars :-)

Some notes about this specific location for protesting:

- Burbank Police are supportive of our protest, as long as we stay on the sidewalks and aren't in the street, and please DO NOT BLOCK the driveway entrance. 

- Please don’t stand on the median.

- Please do not use profanity on your signs or from your mouth
Feel free to come up to me with any concerns during (or before) the protest.  

Let's have fun!  
- Joel

title: Tesla Takedown - Lynnwood
description:
Elon Musk is destroying our democracy, and he's using the fortune he built at Tesla to do it. We are taking nonviolent action at Tesla to stop Musk's illegal coup.

Gather outside the Tesla store in Lynnwood to make your voice heard.

Bring your good energy, signs, and friends, and let's keep the pressure going.

There are also protests at 5 other Tesla locations around the region on Saturday and Tuesday. Find them here: www.teslatakedown.com

Tesla Takedown is a peaceful, grassroots protest movement. We oppose violence, vandalism and destruction of property. This protest is a lawful exercise of our First Amendment right to peaceful assembly.

title: No Kings
description:
In America, we don’t put up with would-be kings. NO KINGS is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption from Trump and his allies. We’ve watched as they’ve cracked down on free speech, detained people for their political views, threatened to deport American citizens, and defied the courts. They’ve done this all while continuing to serve and enrich their billionaire allies.

🚨On Saturday, June 14, we’re taking to the streets nationwide. We’re not gathering to feed his ego. We’re building a movement that leaves him behind.🚨

The flag doesn’t belong to Donald Trump. It belongs to us. We’re not watching history happen. We’re making it.

On June 14th, we’re showing up everywhere he isn’t—to say no thrones, no crowns, no kings. Check out nokings.org for more information.

A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

title: Canvass in Middlesex Borough
description:
Join Vincent and the Middlesex Borough Dems as we canvass Middlesex and connect with residents around issues that matter!

We'll meet and walk in the various districts and share Vincent's vision for Middlesex.  As a county committee person representing district 3, he is no stranger to rising to the call and addressing important issues.  So, let's get out and support him to lead Middlesex to change! 

 Sign up today and be part of the movement for a stronger Middlesex!

title: The Torch is Ours:  Protest. Purpose. Power.
description:
Join us for an inspiring evening of reflection, resilience, and resistance. Through powerful storytelling and intergenerational dialogue, we'll hear from those who marched before us—activists from the past whose courage lit the way. They will share their experiences, lessons learned, and wisdom for the road ahead. This is a moment to honor the legacy of protest and pass the torch to a new generation committed to justice, equality, and change.
This event is co-sponsored by Indivisible Lake Norman and Unity in Community.

title: Build Our Volunteer Team in Racine!
description:
Join us for our monthly volunteer recruitment phone banks to call volunteers and build our team in Racine!

If we start building up our volunteer team and connecting with voters this summer, we’ll have the power we need to win critical elections for Democrats next year. 

A great way that you can make a difference is by calling volunteers in our community and inviting them to take action with us. Whether you're an experienced volunteer or a first-time phone banker, we'll make sure you have everything you need for a successful experience. And once you get started, you'll find that phone banking is fun and rewarding!

We need all hands on deck to fight back against Trump and the Republican agenda, so sign up here to join us, and we can't wait to see you there!

title: Pender County Unite for Justice: Live Across NC
description:
It’s all hands on deck to take back our courts for democracy! 

In 2026, we must re-elect champions for our courts up and down the ballot, and our statewide candidates: Justice Anita Earls (NC Supreme Court), Judge John Arrowood (NC Court of Appeals), and Judge Toby Hampson (NC Court of Appeals).

Help us launch their re-election campaigns in style with Justice Allison Riggs and NCDP Chair Anderson Clayton. 

Join us at one of 30 parties happening simultaneously across the state, linked together for one big Zoom to hear from our special guests.

Our very own District Court Judge Ricardo Jensen will join us in person!

title: NEPA Stands Up Troublemakers Cafe: Speak Up! A Zine Workshop
description:
Join NEPA Stands Up for a special Trouble Makers Cafe: Speak Up! A Zine Workshop. Local collage artist, zinester, and NEPASU member Kris K will lead us in making an 8-page minizine out of one sheet of paper.

Zines are small, handmade, often counter-culture self created booklets that can express a message or share art or information. In this fully interactive workshop, you will learn the historical significance of zines, and how accessible materials have been used by marginalized folks to self publish and get their voice heard for over a century. Express what's important to you in your own zine to take with you!

No experience necessary, all supplies provided.

title: Hands Off Veterans March
description:
Join us for a Hands Off Veterans March, in solidarity with veterans protests happening in Washington DC & around the country. 

Our speakers feature veterans of US armed forces. 

Bring your powerful voice and defend our country against all enemies - foreign and domestic.

Optional: Bring your flags, wear your uniform, and prepare to re-take your oath to the constitution. (The oath is optional, and available for anyone regardless of military service.)

WHEN: Friday, June 6 from 5 - 8 PM

WHERE: TX Capitol Front Steps

BRING: Everyone is welcome! Bring your veteran family and friends, plus your creative protest signs 

(NOTE: No sticks longer than 12 inches are allowed by Capitol DPS including flag poles.)

MOBILITY: We will march around the TX Capitol, not outside of Capitol grounds. If you have mobility concerns, you are welcome to stand firm at the front steps of the TX Capitol.

SAFETY: We have a team of volunteers, legal observers, and street medics coming to this event. 

If you would like to volunteer for any of these teams, please use this form to contact us! -- https://bit.ly/VetMarchVols

title: Sunrise Tarrant Hub Retreat
description:
Build Power, Build Tarrant's New Organizing Home!

🗓 May 29–30, 2025
📍Tarrant county, TX (location shared after registration)

Join us for a two-day retreat where we’ll dream big, deepen our bonds, and organize to win. Whether you’re new to the Sunrise Movement or have been holding it down with the Tarrant hub, this retreat is your space to plug in, learn, heal, and build.

We’ll kick things off Thursday night with art, food, and political grounding around Tarrant County’s environmental and political landscape. On Friday, we’ll dive into defining the mission of our hub, mapping our national and local campaigns, and building strong teams to carry out the work — from communications to actions to recruitment. title: New York, NY: Our Next Climate Victory: Passing the NY HEAT Act
description:
The NY HEAT Act is our top climate priority, with its promise of lower energy bills while eliminating massive subsidies to the gas industry.

With the state budget finally done, Albany lawmakers must prioritize passing the NY HEAT Act in the waning weeks of the legislative session

**Join us to learn about opportunities to take action and get involved in passing this policy essential to moving New York off fossil fuels.**

_At the meeting, we'll also discuss our work to ban new factory farms in New York, resist the Trump administration, and enforce Local Law 97, New York City's Green New Deal for buildings._
